commit.message: Makr as compat with 3.9

better wayland session detection

XDG_SESSION_TYPE may not always be set to "wayland" or "x11" depending
on what compositor/setup the user is using. For instance, weston (the
reference compositor) does not set this particular environment variable.
Instead, check for the existence of WAYLAND_DISPLAY. This is set by all
wayland compositors and tells clients which wayland compositor to
connect to. If we have this variable set, we can be sure wayland is
being used.

commit.message: Updated pipfile and Pipfile.lock

Make PyQt checks in tests more specific

Test whether the widgets module can be imported rather than 'PyQt?'
in general.  The latter gives false positives if PyQt is uninstalled
but there are leftover subpackages such as qscintilla.  In this case,
Python 3 imports 'PyQt?' as a namespace.
